Czech Church Council Agrees to Broad State Compensation Proposal

-- B y   L e n k a   P o n i k e l s k a
-- 
2011-08-12T05:39:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-12/czech-church-council-agrees-to-broad-state-compensation-proposal.html
The Czech Ecumenical Council of
Churches agreed to a government proposal to receive back 56
percent of its former property plus 59 billion koruna ($3
billion) in compensation,  CTK  reported, citing Archbishop
Dominik Duka.  The church should receive the amount gradually in the next
20 years, the newswire added.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lenka Ponikelska in Prague at 
 lponikelska1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  